        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Richmond</placeName> <date>April 17. 1852</date>.</p>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Valued Friend&#33;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">If I am not mistaken<lb/> I am indebted to you a reply to your<lb/> esteemed favour of the <date>12th March</date>&#44; the con&#45;<lb/>tents of which was duly noted&#44; and in reply<lb/> regret that any act of mine should have<lb/> proven any wise detrimental to your interest&#44;<lb/> I know &#40;that your good knowledge of&#41; Ger&#45;<lb/>man &#40;Bavarian&#41; liberality in patronizing a<lb/> Journal could not have been much im&#45;<lb/>paired by the publication of the article con&#45;<lb/>cerning the &#34;Beth Haim&#34; I can assure<lb/> you that it did not make one jot<lb/> difference. I have noticed all your<lb/> hints concerning the congregation and hope<lb/> to profit by them.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I see by the letter that <persName>Jacob A. Levy</persName><lb/> recd from you the other day&#44; that you<lb/> anticipate a flare up with the Education<lb/> Society&#44; whilst I know that you main&#45;<lb/>tain correct views and a stickler of<lb/> just principles&#44; I must advise you&#44; to<lb/> desist the opposition to the majority&#44;<lb/> rather retire <sic>peacably</sic> from them than<lb/> to combat with your superior in power&#44;</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>I wish I could see you otherwise situated<lb/> with the Israelites of <placeName>Philada</placeName>. I fear from<lb/> what I can learn that the breach of<lb/> <sic>dissention</sic> is expanding between you and<lb/> them. I have stuck to your views and<lb/> opposition here and would that I was a<lb/> member of &#34;Mickval Israel&#34; to stand<lb/> by you there.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Our new Hefra are about getting<lb/> <persName>Isaac Lyon</persName> to print their constitution and<lb/> it will require some Hebrew type&#44; but<lb/> he has a parcel a proof of which I en&#45;<lb/>close with the size of the type&#44; they lack<lb/> the <add>Hebrew</add> to wit the <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> all the final letters and the stops<lb/> I should like you to send me about<lb/> 12 of each of the above if you can<lb/> get them which will complete the lot<lb/> <persName>Mr Lyons</persName> has in case you cannot<lb/> get them&#44; he wants you to get a<lb/> small font of <hi rend="underline">small pica</hi> say to the<lb/> amount of two or three dollars&#44; if<lb/> you can get the size like the sample<lb/> he would rather have them&#44; whatever<lb/> <sic>expence</sic> may attend the execution of<lb/> this order <persName>Mr Mailert</persName> will forward<lb/> to you&#44; nothing more but remain as<lb/> ever yours truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Jacob Ezekiel</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
